Prior studies have explored the form of U that is most bioavailable across several species, such as algae20, Arabidopsis thaliana14,21, Brassica juncea22, and many others. In all cases it has been found that U in the form of the uranyl ion (UO22+\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
