				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\sim $$\end{document}700 ps–1 ns upon fs-laser excitation40–43. Here, we define the fluorescence lifetime as the constant of the exponential fit, i.e., the time it takes the fluorescence intensity to drop to 1/e ×\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
